## ðŸ“ Basic Markdown Syntax

| Markdown Syntax        | Description                        | Example                           |
|------------------------|------------------------------------|-----------------------------------|
 `#`                    | Heading 1 (H1)                     | `# My Title`                      |
| `##`                   | Heading 2 (H2)                     | `## Subtitle`                     |
| `###`                  | Heading 3 (H3)                     | `### Section`                     |
| `**bold**`             | Bold text                          | `**important**` â†’ **important**   |
| `*italic*`             | Italic text                        | `*emphasis*` â†’ *emphasis*         |
| `~~strikethrough~~`    | Strikethrough                      | `~~deleted~~` â†’ ~~deleted~~       |
| \`inline code\`        | Inline code                        | \`console.log()\` â†’ `console.log()` |
| \`\`\`code block\`\`\` | Code block (use 3 backticks)       | See below                         |
| `> quote`              | Blockquote                         | > This is a quote                 |
| `-`, `+`, or `*`       | Unordered list                     | `- Item`                          |
| `1.`                   | Ordered list                       | `1. First item`                   |
| `[text](url)`          | Link                               | `[Astro](https://astro.build)`    |
| `![alt](image-url)`    | Image                              | `![Logo](logo.png)`               |
| `---`                  | Horizontal line                    | Creates a divider                 |

